for Pier 32.

242
00:22:53,866 --> 00:22:56,488
Thank you.

243
00:22:56,578 --> 00:22:59,114
l've heard police work is dangerous.

244
00:22:59,203 --> 00:23:01,530
Yes, that's why l carry a big gun.

245
00:23:02,083 --> 00:23:04,454
Couldn't it go off accidentally?

246
00:23:04,543 --> 00:23:06,833
l used to have that problem.

247
00:23:06,921 --> 00:23:08,961
What did you do about it?

248
00:23:09,048 --> 00:23:11,542
l just think about baseball.

249
00:23:13,346 --> 00:23:16,632
That's a honey of an ankle-bracelet
you have there.

250
00:23:16,725 --> 00:23:19,512
Did it slip down there again?

251
00:23:19,604 --> 00:23:22,475
Yes, well...
l'll quickly go through these

252
00:23:22,566 --> 00:23:24,605
and get them back to you tomorrow.

253
00:23:24,693 --> 00:23:29,355
Fine, but there's no rush.
l mean, whenever you're through.

254
00:23:29,449 --> 00:23:33,613
Thank you. l wish there was
some way l could repay you.

255
00:23:33,702 --> 00:23:38,911
How about dinner? l know a place
that serves great Viking food.

256
00:23:39,002 --> 00:23:43,131
lt's tempting, but l'm afraid
l must rest this evening,

257
00:23:43,216 --> 00:23:45,255
tomorrow being Arbor Day.

258
00:23:45,342 --> 00:23:48,212
Of course. Perhaps some other time.

259
00:23:48,303 --> 00:23:51,887
- How about a rain check?
- Let's just stick to dinner.

260
00:23:51,974 --> 00:23:55,594
Thank you for your help,
Miss Spencer.

261
00:23:56,939 --> 00:23:58,978
My pleasure.

262
00:23:59,066 --> 00:24:02,733
- Well?
- Mr Ludwig, you startled me!

263
00:24:02,822 --> 00:24:04,695
l'm sorry, my dear.

264
00:24:04,783 --> 00:24:07,948
Did you give the lieutenant
what he wanted?

265
00:24:08,034 --> 00:24:10,610
l gave him copies of the files
for Pier 32.

266
00:24:10,706 --> 00:24:12,745
Good. That's good.

267
00:24:12,832 --> 00:24:17,828
He is an intriguing fellow,
don't you think?

268
00:24:17,922 --> 00:24:21,920
Well, l don't know.
l've only just met him.

269
00:24:22,010 --> 00:24:23,883
He seems very nice.

270
00:24:23,970 --> 00:24:27,175
Jane, l realise
this is an unusual request,

271
00:24:27,267 --> 00:24:30,600
but if there is something illegal
going on in this company,

272
00:24:30,687 --> 00:24:34,474
l need to know about it,
so we can root it out.

273
00:24:34,567 --> 00:24:36,642
That's why l want you to...

274
00:24:36,735 --> 00:24:40,984
well, to get to know Drebin
a little better,

275
00:24:41,074 --> 00:24:43,115
find out what he knows.

276
00:24:43,203 --> 00:24:45,989
Wouldn't this be best handled
by the police?

277
00:24:46,079 --> 00:24:49,416
We are letting the police handle it,
my dear!

278
00:24:49,501 --> 00:24:52,585
But we need to know
the facts quickly

279
00:24:52,671 --> 00:24:55,792
before anything
gets into the newspapers.

280
00:24:55,883 --> 00:25:00,345
Don't forget, l have a responsibility
to the stockholders.

281
00:25:00,432 --> 00:25:03,967
Well...if you put it that way...

282
00:25:04,061 --> 00:25:07,974
- Yes, l'll do my best.
- That's better.

283
00:25:11,026 --> 00:25:13,945
l'm sure you will.

284
00:25:19,202 --> 00:25:23,534
lt was about 4pm
when l returned to Police Squad.

285
00:25:23,625 --> 00:25:28,253
l wanted to see what the lab had
come up with on Nordberg's jacket,

286
00:25:28,339 --> 00:25:30,794
the one they'd found on the docks.

287
00:25:30,883 --> 00:25:34,585
You can tell a lot from fibre
samples if they aren't too wet.

288
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:37,253
l was hoping we wouldn't
come up dry.

289
00:25:37,349 --> 00:25:38,974
Hey, look out!

290
00:25:41,229 --> 00:25:42,974
Police! Halt!

291
00:25:51,908 --> 00:25:54,779
Anybody catch the licence plate?

292
00:25:55,203 --> 00:25:58,288
Anybody get a look at the driver?

293
00:26:01,712 --> 00:26:04,997
Take the names of everybody here
for questioning.

294
00:26:05,090 --> 00:26:08,875
l've got to get...inside.

295
00:26:15,644 --> 00:26:19,015
Hi, Ed, Ted. You got
those fibre samples yet?

296
00:26:19,106 --> 00:26:21,184
- We got some action here.
- What?

297
00:26:21,277 --> 00:26:23,733
We're testing our anti-graffiti wall.

298
00:26:23,822 --> 00:26:25,694
We've got customers.

299
00:26:25,780 --> 00:26:29,482
lt reacts when
the spray hits the sensors.

300
00:26:32,748 --> 00:26:34,991
You've done it again - mazel tov!

301
00:26:35,083 --> 00:26:37,872
Good work.
What will you think of next?

302
00:26:37,963 --> 00:26:40,002
Now that you mention it,

303
00:26:40,089 --> 00:26:42,961
here's something
we developed only yesterday.

304
00:26:43,052 --> 00:26:45,887
To the casual observer -
an ordinary shoe.

305
00:26:45,972 --> 00:26:49,886
But in actuality...
it makes a handy weapon.

306
00:26:49,977 --> 00:26:53,227
And everything a cop would need.

307
00:26:53,314 --> 00:26:55,390
We call it the Swiss Army Shoe.

308
00:26:55,484 --> 00:27:00,062
- Great. And the fibre samples?
- Just one more thing.

309
00:27:00,155 --> 00:27:02,444
See these cufflinks l'm wearing?

310
00:27:02,532 --> 00:27:07,195
They're not just cufflinks. Each one
fires a single pin-sized dart,

311
00:27:07,289 --> 00:27:10,374
that knocks out your victim
for a few minutes.

312
00:27:10,460 --> 00:27:12,702
Let me demonstrate on Ed.

313
00:27:14,671 --> 00:27:17,377
Ted! Why?

314
00:27:19,302 --> 00:27:22,388
Don't worry.
He'll be up and around in no time.

315
00:27:22,474 --> 00:27:26,602
- Why don't you take a pair?
- Actually, l could use another pair.

316
00:27:26,687 --> 00:27:28,560
l think you'll like them.

317
00:27:28,648 --> 00:27:31,400
- Want this, chief?
- Thank you, Al.

318
00:27:31,483 --> 00:27:34,568
There's something
on the side of your mouth, Al.

319
00:27:34,654 --> 00:27:37,193
No, no. The other side.

320
00:27:37,282 --> 00:27:41,992
As you requested, we took some
fibre samples from Nordberg's jacket.

321
00:27:42,079 --> 00:27:44,487
l'm afraid it doesn't look good.

322
00:27:44,583 --> 00:27:48,081
- What do you mean?
- Take a look for yourself.

323
00:27:50,673 --> 00:27:54,588
- l can't see anything.
- Use your open eye, Frank.

324
00:27:55,303 --> 00:27:57,343
Yeah, l can see it now.

325
00:27:57,430 --> 00:28:01,015
At first, it appears
to be the normal cotton fibres.

326
00:28:01,102 --> 00:28:03,806
But we discovered
a fine white powder.

327
00:28:05,316 --> 00:28:07,641
Pure heroin.

328
00:28:07,734 --> 00:28:10,820
How well do you know Nordberg?

329
00:28:10,905 --> 00:28:14,488
We were partners for nine years
and he's my best friend.

330
00:28:14,576 --> 00:28:17,993
We can't allow personal feelings
to get in the way.

331
00:28:18,081 --> 00:28:22,827
- Are you saying that Nordberg...?
- The Queen arrives in two days.

332
00:28:22,920 --> 00:28:25,459
lf the press should pick this up,

333
00:28:25,547 --> 00:28:28,632
it could be embarrassing
for the police and the city.

334
00:28:28,718 --> 00:28:32,965
l'm sorry, Frank. l'm giving you
24 hours to clear Nordberg.

335
00:28:43,486 --> 00:28:45,525
- Mr Ludwig?
- Yes?

336
00:28:45,612 --> 00:28:50,241
- A Mr Pahpshmir is here.
- Show him in.

337
00:28:57,460 --> 00:29:00,547
ls there something wrong, Mr Ludwig?

338
00:29:00,632 --> 00:29:02,374
No, it's nothing.

339
00:29:02,465 --> 00:29:06,714
- Then may we get down to business?
- Certainly. Have a seat.

340
00:29:06,805 --> 00:29:09,924
l can carry out your request.

341
00:29:10,016 --> 00:29:14,266
- My price is $20 million.
- Your price is not a problem.

342
00:29:15,940 --> 00:29:19,690
But there is concern
on the part of those l represent,

343
00:29:19,778 --> 00:29:25,569
that you would be able to...
complete so difficult a task.

344
00:29:25,659 --> 00:29:28,034
Tell me, Mr Pahpshmir,

345
00:29:28,121 --> 00:29:33,710
in all the world,
who is the most effective assassin?

346
00:29:33,796 --> 00:29:39,301
l would think anyone who manages to
conceal his identity as an assassin.

347
00:29:39,384 --> 00:29:44,344
Yes, but there is
even a more ideal assassin.

348
00:29:46,435 --> 00:29:50,681
One who doesn't know
he is an assassin.

349
00:29:50,773 --> 00:29:53,443
- Care for some tea?
- Yes, please.

350
00:29:53,527 --> 00:29:56,646
Dominique, service for two, please.

351
00:30:08,211 --> 00:30:10,916
l must kill Pahpshmir.

352
00:30:18,931 --> 00:30:22,681
- Cream and sugar, sir?
- Mr Pahpshmir?

353
00:30:26,398 --> 00:30:28,557
Cream only, please.

354
00:30:30,320 --> 00:30:34,448
- There's a gun on the floor, sir!
- Just leave it. lt's all right.

355
00:30:34,533 --> 00:30:37,784
- The tea, please.
- Of course, sir.

356
00:30:39,746 --> 00:30:44,291
Mr Pahpshmir, have you ever seen
sensory-induced hypnosis?

357
00:30:44,378 --> 00:30:46,418
l think l just have.

358
00:30:46,505 --> 00:30:49,258
How will she get near the target?

359
00:30:49,341 --> 00:30:53,292
Oh, l doubt whether it will be her.

360
00:30:53,389 --> 00:30:57,091
Good secretaries
are so hard to find these days.

361
00:30:57,185 --> 00:30:59,808
And it seems to me...

362
00:31:01,065 --> 00:31:04,434
anyone...can be an assassin.

363
00:31:07,906 --> 00:31:12,569
l had 24 hours to find
something to clear my friend's name.

364
00:31:12,660 --> 00:31:15,616
l returned to the hospital
with Ludwig's records

365
00:31:15,707 --> 00:31:18,199
to try to jog Nordberg's memory.

366
00:31:18,293 --> 00:31:21,995
Doctor, l have the chart,
if you're ready to go over it.

367
00:31:22,090 --> 00:31:25,209
l'll be with you
when l've finished with Mr Nordberg.

368
00:31:25,301 --> 00:31:27,377
Yes, Doctor.

369
00:31:32,937 --> 00:31:35,605
You'll be out of here
in a couple of...

370
00:31:41,655 --> 00:31:45,439
- l'd like to see Officer Nordberg.
- Sign in, please.

371
00:31:45,533 --> 00:31:48,868
Wait a minute!
Where's the police guard?

372
00:31:48,954 --> 00:31:52,903
- Drebin called and sent him home.
- Drebin?

373
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:58,625
l must kill Nordberg.
l must kill Nordberg.

374
00:31:58,716 --> 00:32:01,965
Drebin, Police Squad!
Let go of that pillow!

375
00:32:31,420 --> 00:32:34,293
Medical emergency!

376
00:32:40,723 --> 00:32:44,473
Drebin, Police Squad.
Follow that black car!

377
00:32:46,315 --> 00:32:48,472
The car! Follow that car!

378
00:32:48,566 --> 00:32:52,184
Stephanie, check your mirror. Signal.

379
00:32:52,277 --> 00:32:54,734
Now pull into traffic.

380
00:32:57,909 --> 00:33:00,071
Try and ease off on the brake.

381
00:33:02,332 --> 00:33:06,378
- Give it a little gas.
- l know a short cut. Turn left here!

382
00:33:09,716 --> 00:33:12,090
- There he is!
- Easy!

383
00:33:27,196 --> 00:33:28,939
Turn right! Follow him!

384
00:33:29,031 --> 00:33:32,947
lt's OK.
Normally, you would not be going 65

385
00:33:33,035 --> 00:33:36,119
down the wrong way
of a one-way street.

386
00:33:38,041 --> 00:33:40,081
Apply the brakes.

387
00:33:41,045 --> 00:33:42,872
Now put it in reverse.

388
00:33:50,390 --> 00:33:52,797
- You dumb broad!
- Stephanie...

389
00:33:52,891 --> 00:33:55,099
Gently extend your arm.

390
00:33:56,812 --> 00:34:00,265
Extend your middle finger.

391
00:34:03,029 --> 00:34:06,115
- Very good. Well done.
- There he is!

392
00:34:06,200 --> 00:34:08,656
Go for it, Stephanie!

393
00:34:53,840 --> 00:34:55,747
Excuse me. Excuse me.

394
00:34:55,840 --> 00:34:59,294
All right, move on!
Nothing to see here!

395
00:34:59,388 --> 00:35:01,843
Please disperse!

396
00:35:01,932 --> 00:35:04,469
Nothing to see here. Please!

397
00:35:06,854 --> 00:35:11,399
The attempt on Nordberg's
life left me shaken and disturbed.

398
00:35:11,485 --> 00:35:14,355
The questions kept coming up
again and again,

399
00:35:14,446 --> 00:35:16,525
like bubbles in a case of soda.

400
00:35:17,575 --> 00:35:19,948
Who was this character
in the hospital?

401
00:35:20,036 --> 00:35:23,869
Why was he trying to kill
Nordberg...and for whom?

402
00:35:23,956 --> 00:35:27,872
Did Ludwig lie to me?
l didn't have any proof,

403
00:35:27,962 --> 00:35:30,536
but somehow,
l didn't entirely trust him.

404
00:35:30,632 --> 00:35:34,417
Why was the ''l Luv You''
not listed in Ludwig's records?

405
00:35:34,511 --> 00:35:37,264
lf it was, did he know about it?

406
00:35:37,349 --> 00:35:39,592
lf he didn't, who did?

407
00:35:39,684 --> 00:35:41,891
And where the hell was l?

408
00:35:44,857 --> 00:35:47,479
lt was almost midnight
when l got home.

409
00:35:47,568 --> 00:35:50,321
l just wanted
to slip under my blankets,

410
00:35:50,406 --> 00:35:53,823
but my night was
just about to begin.

411
00:36:32,623 --> 00:36:35,079
You're late.

412
00:36:36,251 --> 00:36:38,920
That depends on what l'm late for.

413
00:36:39,004 --> 00:36:42,090
You said we should
have dinner some time.

414
00:36:42,176 --> 00:36:45,046
Tonight became ''some time''.

415
00:36:46,513 --> 00:36:48,672
l'm boiling a roast.

416
00:36:50,936 --> 00:36:53,426
How hot and wet do you like it?

417
00:36:53,520 --> 00:36:58,764
Very hot and awfully wet.

418
00:36:58,862 --> 00:37:02,610
You seem to know your way
around a kitchen.

419
00:37:02,699 --> 00:37:06,151
l'm just as handy
in other rooms of the house.

420
00:37:06,246 --> 00:37:08,570
That shirt looks familiar.

421
00:37:08,664 --> 00:37:12,912
lt's yours. l didn't want
to get stained or wrinkled.

422
00:37:13,003 --> 00:37:16,004
At least...not yet.

423
00:37:19,262 --> 00:37:23,305
Do you mind if l slip
into something more comfortable?

424
00:37:29,648 --> 00:37:32,140
There. That's better.

425
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:37,357
l hope you've brought your appetite.

426
00:37:37,449 --> 00:37:39,323
l've brought everything.

427
00:37:39,410 --> 00:37:42,031
Well, then, dig in.

428
00:37:46,835 --> 00:37:51,378
lnteresting. Almost as interesting
as the photographs l saw today.

429
00:37:51,464 --> 00:37:53,839
l was young. l needed the work.

430
00:37:53,926 --> 00:37:57,047
No, they were taken
at Ludwig's docks.

431
00:37:57,138 --> 00:38:01,385
A ship came in, a Panamanian ship.
lt wasn't on Ludwig's records.

432
00:38:01,478 --> 00:38:03,765
Probably an oversight.

433
00:38:03,855 --> 00:38:07,187
How is your...meat?

434
00:38:10,238 --> 00:38:12,312
You be the judge of that.

435
00:38:15,993 --> 00:38:17,406
Mmm...

436
00:38:20,207 --> 00:38:22,663
l've got nine more.

437
00:38:27,591 --> 00:38:30,260
- Have you seen that ship?
- l don't know.

438
00:38:30,344 --> 00:38:34,176
lt doesn't look like ours,
but we deal with so many ships.

439
00:38:34,265 --> 00:38:37,183
Has Officer Nordberg
told you anything?

440
00:38:37,268 --> 00:38:41,314
No, there's been another attempt
on his life. He's in a coma.

441
00:38:41,399 --> 00:38:45,693
That's terrible!
This world is such a violent place.

442
00:38:45,779 --> 00:38:48,485
lf it wasn't, l'd be out of a job,

443
00:38:48,576 --> 00:38:53,284
but l'd give it up tomorrow
to live in a world without crime.

444
00:38:54,499 --> 00:38:56,537
That's beautiful.

445
00:38:59,755 --> 00:39:02,590
This is all happening too fast.

446
00:39:05,344 --> 00:39:09,009
- l've been hurt before.
- l'm sorry.

447
00:39:11,518 --> 00:39:13,557
l'd known her for years.

448
00:39:13,645 --> 00:39:17,016
We used to go to
all the police functions together.

449
00:39:17,107 --> 00:39:20,311
How l loved her,
but she had her music.

450
00:39:20,403 --> 00:39:23,192
l think she had her music.

451
00:39:23,281 --> 00:39:27,066
She'd hang out with the
Chicago Male Chorus and Symphony.

452
00:39:27,161 --> 00:39:31,206
l don't recall her playing
an instrument or being able to sing.

453
00:39:31,291 --> 00:39:34,247
Yet she was on the road
300 days of the year.

454
00:39:34,336 --> 00:39:39,414
l bought her a harp for Christmas.
She asked me what it was.

455
00:39:41,845 --> 00:39:44,301
lt's the same old story.
Boy finds girl.

456
00:39:44,389 --> 00:39:47,059
Boy loses girl. Girl finds boy.

457
00:39:47,144 --> 00:39:50,227
Boy forgets girl. Boy remembers girl.

458
00:39:50,313 --> 00:39:52,556
Girl dies in a blimp accident

459
00:39:52,650 --> 00:39:55,521
over the Orange Bowl
on New Year's Day.

460
00:39:55,612 --> 00:39:58,696
- Goodyear?
- No, the worst.

461
00:39:58,782 --> 00:40:00,526
Poor dear!

462
00:40:03,912 --> 00:40:07,330
Now, now. l don't want to upset you.

463
00:40:07,416 --> 00:40:10,419
Frank, it's not that.

464
00:40:10,504 --> 00:40:12,912
Why did you have to be so wonderful?

465
00:40:14,467 --> 00:40:19,260
- There's something l must tell you.
- No! No need to tell me anything.

466
00:40:19,347 --> 00:40:22,265
What's in the past
doesn't matter anyway.

467
00:40:22,352 --> 00:40:23,762
Maybe...

468
00:40:23,853 --> 00:40:28,812
Maybe we're just two lonely souls
who have found each other.

469
00:40:32,697 --> 00:40:35,105
Funny-face!

470
00:40:52,886 --> 00:40:56,553
l want you to know...
l practise safe sex.

471
00:40:56,641 --> 00:40:58,385
So do l.

472
00:42:32,253 --> 00:42:36,798
l had a wonderful day, Frank. l can't
believe we just met yesterday.

473
00:42:37,678 --> 00:42:40,763
You really mean that?
You're not just saying it,

474
00:42:40,846 --> 00:42:43,303
because we exchanged bodily fluids?

475
00:42:43,393 --> 00:42:46,762
No, l really mean it.
You're very special.

476
00:42:46,855 --> 00:42:51,185
- Can l interest you in a nightcap?
- No, thanks, l don't wear them.

477
00:42:51,277 --> 00:42:53,602
Actually, l'm on stake-out tonight.

478
00:42:53,697 --> 00:42:57,612
l'll be thinking about you.
l'll call you tomorrow.

479
00:42:58,869 --> 00:43:00,413
OK.

480
00:43:06,920 --> 00:43:08,960
Good night!

481
00:43:19,311 --> 00:43:22,396
The answer's up there
in Ludwig's office.

482
00:43:22,482 --> 00:43:25,435
Call it what you will -
a hunch, women's intuition.

483
00:43:25,525 --> 00:43:27,733
Ludwig knows more than he's saying.

484
00:43:27,821 --> 00:43:31,818
A hunch won't stand up in court.
Where are your hard facts?

485
00:43:31,909 --> 00:43:35,776
He's the only one except us
who knew Nordberg was still alive.

486
00:43:35,871 --> 00:43:40,333
Next thing we know,
some thug tries to knock him off.

