before the seventh inning stretch.

726
01:11:58,546 --> 01:12:03,041
You're going to have to stall them.
Don't let 'em get that third out.

727
01:12:03,134 --> 01:12:04,797
Right.

728
01:12:06,390 --> 01:12:12,310
The Mariners' number four -
Armando Criscione! Criscione!

729
01:12:19,530 --> 01:12:22,484
- Ball!
- Ball?

730
01:12:32,921 --> 01:12:34,545
Ball!

731
01:12:45,811 --> 01:12:48,480
Get...get...what the...? Get off!

732
01:12:49,565 --> 01:12:51,604
Catch it! Catch it!

733
01:12:56,072 --> 01:12:58,149
- Get 'em off!
- Go, go, go!

734
01:13:02,412 --> 01:13:05,037
- Safe!
- What do you mean, safe?

735
01:13:05,125 --> 01:13:07,249
l don't believe it!

736
01:13:09,337 --> 01:13:11,166
Second base! On two!

737
01:13:12,341 --> 01:13:14,417
There's a throw by the catcher

738
01:13:14,511 --> 01:13:17,927
and now they've got Criscione
hung up between 1st and 2nd!

739
01:13:18,015 --> 01:13:20,138
What the hell are you doing?

740
01:13:20,226 --> 01:13:21,389
What?

741
01:13:21,478 --> 01:13:26,271
- You're not supposed to do that!
- Wait a minute! Stop that!

742
01:13:26,358 --> 01:13:29,063
Put that back down! Give me the ball!

743
01:13:31,698 --> 01:13:33,323
l'll get you!

744
01:13:33,409 --> 01:13:35,697
lt's hard to believe,

745
01:13:35,785 --> 01:13:39,487
but apparently the umpires
have got Criscione in a run-down!

746
01:13:42,211 --> 01:13:43,955
- Safe!
- Safe?

747
01:13:44,046 --> 01:13:45,457
How about that?

748
01:13:45,548 --> 01:13:47,374
- Out!
- Safe!

749
01:13:47,465 --> 01:13:49,461
- Out!
- He was safe!

750
01:13:49,552 --> 01:13:50,750
- Out!
- Safe!

751
01:13:50,845 --> 01:13:53,337
There's a sight l've never seen!

752
01:13:55,101 --> 01:13:57,058
- Safe!
- What are you doing?

753
01:13:57,143 --> 01:13:58,687
Safe! Safe! Safe!

754
01:13:58,771 --> 01:14:01,558
- He was out!
- He was safe!

755
01:14:01,650 --> 01:14:04,439
You idiot! He was out!

756
01:14:04,527 --> 01:14:06,902
All right, you're out of here!

757
01:14:06,988 --> 01:14:10,076
- What?
- You can't throw an umpire out!

758
01:14:10,160 --> 01:14:12,699
All right, YOU'RE out!

759
01:14:13,790 --> 01:14:17,954
Hold on! Even the guy running
the scoreboard says he was out!

760
01:14:18,044 --> 01:14:21,380
And he's up in the mezzanine!

761
01:14:21,465 --> 01:14:22,877
lt's the third out!

762
01:14:40,236 --> 01:14:43,358
l must kill...the Queen.

763
01:14:48,038 --> 01:14:50,612
l must kill...the Queen.

764
01:14:53,335 --> 01:14:55,376
Frank, it's the right-fielder!

765
01:15:01,679 --> 01:15:05,428
- You're the boss!
- lt was safe.

766
01:15:05,518 --> 01:15:08,090
Now, we're going to take a walk.

767
01:15:08,477 --> 01:15:11,351
How could you
do something so vicious?

768
01:15:11,442 --> 01:15:16,318
lt was easy. Don't forget l spent
two years as a building contractor.

769
01:15:16,405 --> 01:15:18,646
Now, let's go quietly.

770
01:15:23,162 --> 01:15:25,239
Hey, look at that! Let's get him!

771
01:15:36,512 --> 01:15:38,719
Kick him in the balls!

772
01:16:11,720 --> 01:16:14,720
l must kill...the Queen.

773
01:16:25,820 --> 01:16:27,647
Look out!

774
01:16:32,661 --> 01:16:36,991
The umpire...
He saved the Queen's life!

775
01:16:37,083 --> 01:16:39,122
That's not the umpire, Your Honour.

776
01:16:43,298 --> 01:16:45,338
Hey, it's Enrico Pallazzo!

777
01:16:56,313 --> 01:16:59,400
Frank! Frank, help!

778
01:16:59,485 --> 01:17:02,485
Frank! Frank, help! Frank!

779
01:17:17,254 --> 01:17:19,165
Hold it, Ludwig!

780
01:17:19,258 --> 01:17:21,631
Stay where you are!

781
01:17:21,719 --> 01:17:24,175
- He's got a gun!
- l know.

782
01:17:24,264 --> 01:17:27,965
You ruined my life.
Now l'm going to ruin yours.

783
01:17:28,061 --> 01:17:31,061
- Leave the girl alone!
- l am. l'm going to kill you.

784
01:17:31,146 --> 01:17:33,187
l see.

785
01:17:36,611 --> 01:17:38,819
Two can play at that game!

786
01:17:45,371 --> 01:17:48,244
- You killed him!
- No, just stunned.

787
01:17:48,334 --> 01:17:50,290
He'll be all right.

788
01:17:56,676 --> 01:17:58,504
Well...

789
01:18:23,959 --> 01:18:27,046
Frank...it's horrible!

790
01:18:28,256 --> 01:18:32,386
- lt's so horrible!
- l know, Ed.

791
01:18:33,011 --> 01:18:35,051
My father went the same way.

792
01:18:50,741 --> 01:18:54,953
l must kill...Frank Drebin.

793
01:18:55,038 --> 01:18:58,122
l must kill...Frank Drebin.

794
01:18:59,210 --> 01:19:01,452
No, no, don't shoot!

795
01:19:01,796 --> 01:19:05,663
Jane...it's me...

796
01:19:08,011 --> 01:19:09,422
Funny-face.

797
01:19:09,513 --> 01:19:13,346
l must kill Frank Drebin.

798
01:19:13,435 --> 01:19:16,221
You love Frank Drebin.

799
01:19:16,313 --> 01:19:19,314
And Frank Drebin loves you.

800
01:19:19,399 --> 01:19:23,314
Jane, if you don't love me,
you might as well pull that trigger,

801
01:19:23,404 --> 01:19:29,194
because without you,
l wouldn't want to live anyway.

802
01:19:29,286 --> 01:19:32,739
l've finally found
someone l can love -

803
01:19:32,833 --> 01:19:36,997
a good, clean love...
without utensils.

804
01:19:37,085 --> 01:19:39,922
l must kill Frank Drebin.

805
01:19:41,092 --> 01:19:43,464
lt's a topsy-turvy world, Jane,

806
01:19:43,553 --> 01:19:48,181
and maybe the problems of two people
don't amount to a hill of beans,

807
01:19:48,267 --> 01:19:51,801
but this is our hill
and these are our beans.

808
01:19:53,314 --> 01:19:57,859
Since l met you, l've noticed
things l never knew where there -

809
01:19:57,943 --> 01:20:01,694
birds singing, dew glistening
on a newly-formed leaf,

810
01:20:01,784 --> 01:20:04,155
stop lights...

811
01:20:04,244 --> 01:20:05,905
l must kill...

812
01:20:05,997 --> 01:20:09,365
Jane, this morning...

813
01:20:09,457 --> 01:20:13,670
l bought something for you.
lt's not very much,

814
01:20:13,755 --> 01:20:18,881
but pretty good
for an honest policeman's salary.

815
01:20:18,970 --> 01:20:20,929
lt's an engagement ring.

816
01:20:21,014 --> 01:20:23,054
l'd have given it to you earlier,

817
01:20:23,142 --> 01:20:26,392
but l wanted to wait
until we were alone.

818
01:20:30,566 --> 01:20:33,568
- l...
- l love you, Jane.

819
01:20:38,993 --> 01:20:40,821
Oh, Frank!

820
01:20:53,259 --> 01:20:55,503
l'm sorry!

821
01:21:06,110 --> 01:21:10,605
l'm sorry that l yelled at you
yesterday, l really am.

822
01:21:12,574 --> 01:21:13,951
Drebin!

823
01:21:14,034 --> 01:21:16,704
l was wrong about you.

824
01:21:16,788 --> 01:21:20,917
This city and the whole world
owes you a debt of gratitude.

825
01:21:21,002 --> 01:21:22,200
Thank you.

826
01:21:22,295 --> 01:21:25,628
And Monday morning
we want you back at Police Squad...

827
01:21:25,716 --> 01:21:29,713
- with a promotion to captain.
- Mayor...

828
01:21:29,803 --> 01:21:34,513
Don't thank me. There's someone else
here who wants to thank you.

829
01:21:34,601 --> 01:21:36,972
- Nordberg!
- Hiya, buddy!

830
01:21:37,061 --> 01:21:39,933
The doc says
l should be on my feet in a week!

831
01:21:40,023 --> 01:21:43,939
- And back on the Force!
- Nordberg, that's wonderful!

832
01:21:45,280 --> 01:21:48,568
Frank! Everyone should have
a friend like you!

